TIPS FOR RENTERS<ql>
<m4> TEXT DIVIDED INTO 1 LEG(S) (--)(--) LEG MEASURE SET TO  10p <m2><ql>
<m4> BEGIN LEG #1 <m1> <ep>
<m0>   (box) Get replacement-cost coverage, which will let you buy a new sofa or stereo, rather than actual-value coverage, which will provide only the depreciated value.<ep>
   (box) Review theft limits, and purchase additional coverage if necessary. For instance, many policies only cover jewelry losses of $1,000. <ep>
   (box) Get ``loss of use'' coverage, if possible. If your building is destroyed, this would cover your temporary living expenses. <ep>
   (box) Find out if your policy covers your possessions away from home (in a car, when traveling or in storage) and the limits of that coverage.<ep>
   (box) Ask if a discount is available for storm shutters, burglar alarms or other safety equipment. <ep>
   (box) Document your possessions with photos, videotape or inventory.<ql>
